I'm looking for a caring, trusting, compassionate individual to rent my house and take care of my three cats.  I pay food and costs for the care of the cats, you rent my 800 square foot 2 bedroom octagon home for 1000.00 a month plus electric and gas, I'll pay the water.  Adjacent duplex and triplex units rent from 1200-1400 a month, this is a stand alone home with a 7000 sq ft fenced lot with a big driveway.      It's located at the end of a quiet Spenard cul de sac with an awesome southern exposure, there's lots of room to garden and a big fenced yard for your pooch or more garden beds.   A big sunny deck adds useable outdoor living space in the summer, great for entertaining.  There's a shed for your stuff, washing machine, no dryer, newer appliances includfing a dishwasher.   Walking distance to Connor's Bog, close to bike trails, 3 minutes from the airport, 10 minutes to Downtown or O'Malley.   This is an ideal situation for an urban gardener type, bring your chickens, there's lots of room for them too.  I'm looking for someone who is compassionate with animals,  who I can trust to take care of my cats as if they're your own.  Bring your cat and dog if you have one.      This would be a great place for one person, cozy for two.  If you're the person, I will want to check references and verify employment and criminal history.   I'm looking ideally for someone to do this on  either a short term basis to October 1,  or a long term 2 year basis.    I'm flexible at this point in time as I do have someone who can take over in October.   I'm looking for a March 1st  date to move in.   Thank you for looking, let's chat !!    No emails, no texts, no calls after 9:00 pm please.  Chris 9o7 444-8628

Posting Body:  *********Available NOW*********  Large Two Bedroom, One Bath Unit located directly on Campbell Creek!   This unit is located on the Campbell Creek in a cul-de-sac near the corner of Lake Otis and Tudor. The property location could not be better, as it fronts Campbell Creek on the north side, and is adjacent to TWO parks that are across Homestead Court on the south side and across Lake Otis on the east side. (There are other buildings to the west, but they are separated by the cul-de-sac, so they are not directly adjacent). You can hear the creek rushing by from both of your bedroom windows!   Plenty of parking and a grassy area to enjoy the creek behind the building as well as the two parks across the street. Easy walking access to bike trails, coffee shops and shopping! This is a great place for the working professional!   We are looking for a tenant who will treat the place as their own and feel like they are home (pay rent on time, courteous to neighbors and pass reasonable background check)! The unit features a private south facing deck off the living and dining room! The kitchen is completely remodeled with new cabinets, countertops and tile backsplash. The unit has updated light fixtures and new flooring. New bath vanity, tile backsplash, sink, mirror and commode. Laminate flooring in living room! Bedroom carpet nice and plush!!!   Unit 2A is located on the second floor. Coin operated laundry (recently remodeled with new paint, flooring, lighting and brand new equipment) is located just a few steps away downstairs.   The address is: 2361 Homestead Court, Unit 2A, Anchorage, Alaska 99507. This is in mid-town Anchorage near the University and Providence Hospital, along with two parks across the street, walking trails and shopping!  Rent is $1,200 per month with a security deposit of $1,175. Tenant is responsible for their own Electric statement each month and $45 for cable ("Preferred" package of approximately 200 channels discounted through GCI, regular price is $87.50). We will provide payment for Heat, Hot Water, Trash and all Exterior maintenance. Come see this apartment! It boasts a large floorplan that includes two bedrooms and a bonus space across from the kitchen. There are huge windows that overlook the backyard and a wrap-around porch that really sets this place apart from the competition. You don't have to get rained or snowed on while unloading your groceries from your car to your apartment. Each apartment has their own enclosed storage space in the carport for those extra tires and bicycles. The location of this fourplex is prime. The neighborhood is a mix of small apartment buildings, duplexes, and single family homes. It feels like a neighborhood and not a complex. It is a block away from getting on the fabulous trail system that Anchorage has to offer, particularly close to Taku Lake and the beautiful trails surrounding the lake. Taku Elementary is just two blocks away. It is easy to get around town from this location. Easy access to Dimond via King Street or north/south travel via Old Seward. Minutes from Dimond Center. Landlord is very involved in upkeep and will fix maintenance problems immediately, usually within 24 hours. Landlord also keeps up on snow removal. Please call to schedule a showing. Imagine saving the cost of retail or office space, and going to work by simply walking down your front steps each day into your own private office/retail shop/studio!  PLEASE do not disturb current tenants.  The pictures speak for themselves.  This home is right out of HGTV.  It has been immaculately updated with modern, high-end finishes.  It is located near Seward Meridian & the Palmer-Wasilla Highway, in Wasilla.  It officially has 3 bedrooms, but there could be a 4th room (the downstairs bonus room) which could act as a bedroom for small children.  Granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, large one-bowl stainless steel farmer's apron sink, bamboo hardwood flooring, huge back deck, large fenced yard, open concept, huge master on the main level, TWO bonus rooms, front-loading washer & dryer with a folding area in the utility/laundry room.  Two ceiling fans in Master Bdrm, and one in the main living room & upper bonus room.  The home is partly furnished including a leather sectional sofa, dining room set, nightstands, & end tables if you want them, or there is plenty of room to store those items if not.    This home has mountain views on three sides, and Wal-Mart is only 5 minutes away.   There's a 600-sq-ft, 3-room, attached but SEPARATE, office/shop/retail space with separate entrances at ground level for your small business.  It was formerly a 2-car tandem garage, but has been fully remodeled and presents as a professional office.  It would be suitable for an attorney, accountant, insurance or real estate agent, or any number of other professionals, as well as a retail store-front.  The office has high-end vinyl plank flooring and two entrances, front and rear, and there's room for 6-8 customer cars.  We are currently having a small powder room installed in the office also (which will be completed by January 5), with a toilet and sink.  It is a fully-self-contained office and can be used for all sorts of business activities.  With literally THOUSANDS of potential customers or clients driving by this house every day, (although it is on a parallel access road) the possibilities for any business are endless here!  You could even place a sign above the front office door, which is at street level.     There's a 2-3 horse capacity barn, tack room, and hay storage area which could once again be fenced with your horse fencing -- or it can be used for storage.  There's a large, grassy, fenced backyard for your dog.  There's a large, fenced-off garden plot ready for next season's vegetable planting.  Pets may be allowed on approval.  There is no garage (it's been converted into the office/shop), but there is plenty of parking, including RV parking, and a 50 amp outlet for an RV.  This home is not on the market for sale at the moment, but may be put on the market sometime in 2020.  Because it's a unique property with a commercial emphasis, it will take a unique buyer and is likely to be on the market for a long time.  What this means for you, is that while you may be asked to preapprove the occasional viewing or Open House, it will not be a constant thing.     If this house is put on the market, you will be asked to keep the house clean, to keep up the property inside & out, with lawn mowing, flower-watering, snow plowing, weed-whacking, etc., (in other words, to be responsible tenants as if this was your own home) and to reasonably pre-approve all viewings with a minimum 24-hour notice, or reasonably reschedule them to a more convenient time, and to be absent from the home with your pets(s) when the Buyer's Agent shows up.  Also, smoking will only be allowed outside the home, and cigarette butts need to be contained and discarded.  You may use the Office / Retail Space for your retail/wholesale/professional business or craft area, but NOT AS A STORAGE area, and NOT filled to the brim with boxes, etc., since area would be a primary selling feature of the home and needs to be showable as such.  In exchange, you will get to live in this 2,900 sq ft executive home (which would easily normally rent for $2,900 a month) for only $2,295 a month, plus utilities (gas, electric, and trash disposal).  The security deposit is $2,000.  The contract will be month-to-month, but as I mentioned, is likely to be a long-term rental.  If the house does sell, you will be given 45 days from the date the offer is accepted.    We might consider a Rent-To-Own or Lease-Option situation under the right circumstances, for up to 12 months ONLY, while you gather your down payment money, etc.  You must provide a preapproval letter from a lender for $365,950.  Please respond by calling me or preferably via an email letter including:   -- any questions you have   -- your names and dates of birth (so I can run a background check)   -- phone number(s)   -- description of your situation:  how you will afford to pay the rent, when you'd like to move in, what type of pets you have, how many people in your family, and at least two landlord references with phone numbers, along with your full names and dates of birth so I can run a brief background check.    If you've had criminal convictions or evictions, or do not have the income to pay the rent, you will not qualify.   We will get back to you within 24 hrs.  Thanks for your interest!

Do you want a great rate on a great apartment?  Are you looking for a home close to Interior Alaska's best shopping, dining, and entertainment options?  Do you need to be near Ft. Wainwright, Downtown, or the University?  Would you like to be in the heart of Fairbanks without feeling like you're living in the city?  If you answered yes to any of the above, then Willow Woods Apartments is the place for you!  Willow Woods Apartments currently has 2 bedroom apartments available for less than $1000 per month.  With heat, water, sewer, and garbage all included in the rent, this is a deal that can't be beat!  Willow Woods offers comfortable 1- and 2-bedroom apartment homes that provide both accessibility to town and a sense of solitude. With our premier location alongside Creamer's Field Migratory Waterfowl Refuge, Willow Woods Apartments offers the best of the Alaskan outdoors without sacrificing urban conveniences.   During your residency at Willow Woods, you'll find that many of the best shopping, dining, and entertainment options that Fairbanks has to offer are less than ten minutes from your front door. Spend the afternoon strolling the trails that weave through Creamer's Field's 2000+ acres before taking advantage of our property's proximity to downtown and the city's commercial district; experience our short morning commutes to local schools, Ft. Wainwright, and the University of Alaska; and let your worries fall away as you rely on our experienced and professional staff - available 24 hours a day - to take care of your emergency needs.  Prospective tenants of Willow Woods can look forward to the following amenities:  6 exciting floor plans Furnished and unfurnished units available Large balconies in all units Heat, water, sewer, garbage, and cable service included in the rental cost Less than five minutes walk to the Borough Bus Line Dishwashers (available in 2 bedroom units) 24-hr. emergency maintenance and leasing staff On-site laundry facilities Assigned parking with head bolt plugs Less than five minutes from Joy Elementary School  3-15 month leases available. Furnished units available at additional cost.  Prices are subject to change daily. All rates are based on desired lease length and move-in date. Quoted rates are valid for two business days. Please contact Willow Woods for today's rates.  We look forward to meeting you and assisting in making your move a pleasant one.  You are welcome to contact us via email, phone or fax if you have any questions or need more information.  Our office hours are Monday - Friday 9am-6pm AST.
